import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['x'])
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y?')
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lumosity'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lumosity'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lumosity'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['color'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common color in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['color'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label='Most common color: {:.2f}'.format(data['color'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['key'] = data['key'].astype(str)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['key'] == key]['saturation'] for key in data['key'].unique()], labels=data['key'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('Key')
    ax.set_ylabel('Saturation')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of saturation for each key?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
